                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Oct. 5 (PTI): The CISF has begun to upload on its website details of items left behind by passengers at airports to facilitate easy recovery.          
	The paramilitary force, which looks after the security of 57 airports across the country, will also upload details of the relevant contact persons whom a passenger can approach to claim belongings.          
	Passengers can contact the relevant authority directly and collect the valuables after giving ownership proof.          
	Till now, the airport authority was auctioning such unclaimed items three months after the date of recovery.                   
	 Thekkady (PTI): The steersman and a crew member of the boat that sank in the Periyar lake in Thekkady were arrested on Monday. Police said the accident, that claimed 45 lives, happened because of the carelessness of steersman Victor Samuel and sub-crew Anish. They had also allowed overcrowding on the upper deck of the vessel.                  
	 New Delhi: The Ganga clean-up drive will get Rs 15,000 crore over 10 years under a new plan that aims to focus on the entire river basin rather than towns. The money will be utilised to set up better infrastructure to treat effluents and sewage, environment minister Jairam Ramesh said on Monday.                                                                                                                           
